      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to clinical failure modes and regulatory submission requirements.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs mandated by ASTM F1717 and referenced in FDA guidance for spinal implant 510(k) submissions. Each QoI maps directly to a clinically relevant failure mode. Relevance is fully established."
